WEBVTT

00:00:55.024 --> 00:01:00.302
knowing he has and always will
outlive everyone he has ever loved.

00:01:00.326 --> 00:01:02.721
But what if everyone were immortal?

00:01:02.745 --> 00:01:05.185
Well, first off, Earth is only so big.

00:01:05.209 --> 00:01:07.572
So, where would we all live?

00:01:07.596 --> 00:01:08.846
(Grunts)

00:01:08.870 --> 00:01:11.031
"Excuse me!"
"That's my face!"

00:01:11.055 --> 00:01:13.557
"Stop it!"
"Pardon me."

00:01:13.581 --> 00:01:14.606
"Tight in here!"

00:01:14.630 --> 00:01:17.623
Do you remember what you did last year
or when you were five?

00:01:17.647 --> 00:01:19.602
How much of your past have you forgotten?

00:01:19.626 --> 00:01:22.701
If you have trouble remembering
what you did when you were five,

00:01:22.725 --> 00:01:26.251
how will you remember what happened
if you were alive a thousand years ago?

00:01:26.275 --> 00:01:27.305
A million years ago?

00:01:27.329 --> 00:01:29.620
We don't remember every single
detail of our past

00:01:29.644 --> 00:01:31.644
because our brains have a limited capacity